    {
        "user": "URKQXRCAC",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1779871180.928809",
        "client_msg_id": "B91B3134-EEF6-4553-92AD-9AB1B4ECB70F",
        "text": "I like the article. And I fully agree on the remark that (in my words) science is not (and in my opinion should never be) settled. Whenever we learn or experience something new, existing science might need to be adapted.\nThis also holds for general knowledge. The older I get the more the feeling grows that there is so much I do not know. LLMs on the other hand seem to act contrary, everything seems a hard fact in the way it is told. And I think\/seem to see that a lot of people put a lot of trust in these ‘facts’.\nSo the best option for me remains: keep an open mind and think for myself. Not always easy though to not get caught in existing believes and previous experiences.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
