        "client_msg_id": "A7AA81EC-CCE8-4966-9998-BA8F36AE58F1",
        "text": "There are software developers using LLMs without even reading the code they produce, they just manually see if the app works. Are scientists doing this too with just testing some end product? I hope not. Seems like a different problem from software where it's more about the output than finding some novel new way to do things, atleast in app development.",
